==English==

===Verb===
{{head|en|verb|head=to [[write]] [[off]]}}

# {{context|accounting|lang=en}} To [[reduce]] an [[asset]]'s [[book]] [[value]] to [[zero]]
# {{context|accounting|lang=en}} To record an [[expenditure]] as an expense.
# {{context|accounting|lang=en}} To [[remove]] a portion of a [[debt]] or an amount of an [[account]] owed to you counting it as a loss (as a [[gesture]] of [[goodwill]] for example)
# {{context|accounting|lang=en}} To record a [[notional]] expense such as [[amortization]] or [[depreciation]].
# Figuratively, to assign a low value to something.
#: ''When Katya was injured, he '''wrote off''' the team's chances in the finals.''

